        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/175/220",
        "text": [
          "١٧٥. وَقَالَ (عليه ‏السلام): إِذَا هِبْتَ أَمْراًفَقَعْ فِيهِ، فَإِنَّ شِدَّةَ تَوَقِّيهِأَعْظَمُ مِمَّا تَخَافُ مِنْهُ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "175. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, said: When you are afraid of something dive straight into it, because the intensity of abstaining from it is greater (worse) than what you are afraid of."
          ]
        }
      }
